Pressure transducer test Calibrates and checks the inspiratory and expiratory pressure transducers.

The new zero value for the pressure transducers may not differ more than ±6 cm H 2 O from factory calibration.

With the inspiratory pressure transducers used as a reference, a new gain factor is set for the expiratory pressure transducer. The new gain factor may not differ more than ±5% from factory calibration.

During this test, the different subsystems concerned are compared. The difference between the sub- systems must not be more than ±1 cm H 2 O at 60 cm H 2 O.

Expiratory valve coil test. Measures offset and gain in the valve coil.

(BRE + MON)

